SparkSession & Dataframe:

SparkSession is the main gateway to intract with spark.

    - Create Dataframe 
    - Run SQL queries 
    - Read data 
    - Write data 
    - Configure Saprk 


Creating Saprk Session :

from pyspark.sql import SparkSession
spark=SparkSession.builder\
    .appName("MySparkSessionDemo")\
    .master("local[*]")\
    .config("spark.sql.shuffle.partitions","4")\
    .getOrCreate()


SparkSession        Main entry point 
builder             Used to configure session 
appName             Sets application name 
master              Defines execution mode
config              Sets spark config 
getOrcreate         Creates or reuse session 
Spark.stop()        Stop session 


What is Dataframe 

    - A dataframe is a distributed collection of data orginized into rows and columns with a schema 

        - Data is stored in a tabular formate 
        - It has a column names 
        - Each column has datatype 
        - Data is distributed across multiple machines 



RDD had problems :

Problems                        Explanations 

No Schema                       Spark does not know column structure 

More code 

No Query optimization 


Advatanges of dataframe :

Schema              Columns have define type 

Catalyst Optimizer  Automatic query optimization 

Less Code 

Faster processing 



Creating Dataframes :

    1. From Python List 

    data=[
        (1,"A",30,"Mumbai"),
        (2,"B",31,"Delhi"),
        (3,"C",32,"Pune"),
        (4,"D",33,"Bangalore"),
    ]

    Each row: tuple 
    All rows togather = List 


    spark.createDataFrame(data,columns)

    columns=["id","Name","age","City"]


Check Schema :

    df.printSchema()


2. List of Lists 

    data=[
        [1,"A",30,"Mumbai"],
        [2,"B",31,"Delhi"]
    ]

    column=["id","Name","age","City"]


3. From List of Dictionaries 


4. Creating Dataframe From RDD 

    rdd=spark.sparkContext.parallellize([
        (1,"A",30),
        (2,"B",40)

    ])

    df=spark.createDataFrame(rdd,["id","Name","age"])


5. Explicit Schema 

   from pyspark.sql.types import * 

   StructType:

        - Represents the entire Schema 

    StructField

        - Represents one column 



    schema =StructType([
        StructField(column_name,data type,nullable),
        StructField(column_name,data type,nullable),
        StructField(column_name,data type,nullable),
        StructField(column_name,data type,nullable)
    ])
    nullable: True/False 


    StringType          text 
    FloatType


6. RDD → DataFrame conversion

    rdd = spark.sparkContext.parallelize([
    (1,"Ankit",30),
    (2,"Rahul",28),
    (3,"Neha",25)
])

df = spark.createDataFrame(rdd, ["id","name","age"])

Rarely used today but useful when:
	•	working with legacy Spark code
	•	converting RDD pipelines to DataFrame


7. Create DataFrame from CSV File

df = (
    spark.read
    .format("csv")
    .option("header", True)
    .option("inferSchema", True)
    .option("delimiter", ",")
    .option("quote", '"')
    .option("escape", "\\")
    .option("multiLine", False)
    .option("mode", "PERMISSIVE")
    .option("nullValue", "NULL")
    .option("encoding", "UTF-8")
    .option("ignoreLeadingWhiteSpace", True)
    .option("ignoreTrailingWhiteSpace", True)
    .schema(schema)
    .load("path_to_file.csv")
)

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
from pyspark.sql.types import *

schema = StructType([
    StructField("id", IntegerType(), True),
    StructField("name", StringType(), True),
    StructField("age", IntegerType(), True),
    StructField("salary", DoubleType(), True),
    StructField("comment", StringType(), True)
])

df = (
    spark.read
    .format("csv")
    .option("header", True)
    .option("delimiter", ",")
    .option("quote", '"')
    .option("escape", "\\")
    .option("multiLine", False)
    .option("mode", "PERMISSIVE")
    .option("nullValue", "NA")
    .option("encoding", "UTF-8")
    .option("ignoreLeadingWhiteSpace", True)
    .option("ignoreTrailingWhiteSpace", True)
    .schema(schema)
    .load("employee.csv")
)

1. header 

    .option("header",True)

    - This tells spark whether the first row of the CSV file contains column name.

2. InferSchema 

    - .option("InferSchema ",True)

    - Spark tries to guess the datatype of each column automaically by scannning file
    - Without this option, Saprk reads all column as string by default.

   .schema(schema)

3. Delimiter 

    - .option("Delimiter",",")

    - Character seperated the column 
    - Default demiliter in CSV is comma 


What happens if delimiter is Wrong?

    - Spark will read the entrie row as one single column 

4. quote 

    - .option("quote",'"')

    - This tells spark which chacter is used to wrap text value, especially when text contains the dilimiter itself

5. escape 

    .option("escape", "\\")

    - Used when quote chacters appers insie a quoted filed 
    - It helps spark to understand that the quote is part of the text

6. multiLine

    .option("multiline",true)

    - Allow spark to read a feilds that spans multiple lines 


7. Mode 

    - .option("mode", "PERMISSIVE")
    - Controls how spark handles malformed or bad records 

    3 main modes 

    - PERMISSIVE 

        - default mode 
        - When you do not want the whole job to fail becasue of few bad records 

    - DROPMLFORMED 

        - .option("mode", "DROPMLFORMED ")
        - Spark silently drop malformed records 
        - RIsk - May face data loss 

    - FAILFAST 

        - Job fails immediatley when spark finds malformed records 
        - Strict pipelines 


8. NullValue 

    .option("nullValue","NA")

    - Tells spark which value in the file should be treated as null 

    - NA,NULL,null,empty string ,N/A


9. encoding 

    - option("encoding","UTF-8")
    - defines the chacter encoding of the file 

10. .option("ignoreLeadingWhiteSpace", True)
     Removes spaces at the beginning of a value 
     id,name
     1,     A
     2,     B 



11. .option("ignoreTrailingWhiteSpace", True)

    - Removes spaces at the end of value 

        id, name 
        1,A.    
        2,B.    
12. schema 

    - Manually define Dataframe structure 


df.show()
df.printSchema()

Basic Column Transformations

Transformation              Purpose

select()                    Select specific columns
selectExpr()                Select columns using SQL expressions
withColumn()                Add or modify a column
withColumnRenamed()         Rename a column
drop()                      Remove columns
alias()                     Rename column temporarily
cast()                      Change datatype
col()                       Reference column
lit()                       Create constant column


Row Transformations
-------------------

Transformation                  Purpose

select()                        Select specific columns         
selectExpr()                    Select columns using SQL expressions
withColumn()                    Add or modify a column
withColumnRenamed()             Rename a column
drop()                          Remove columns
alias()                         Rename column temporarily
cast()                          Change datatype
col()                           Reference column
lit()                           Create constant column


Row Transformations
-------------------

Transformation              Purpose
filter()                    Filter rows
where()                     Same as filter
distinct()                  Remove duplicate rows
dropDuplicates()            Remove duplicates based on columns
limit()                     Limit number of rows
sample()                    Random sampling
sampleBy()                  Stratified sampling



Sorting Transformations
-----------------------

Transformation              Purpose
sort()                      Sort DataFrame
orderBy()                   Same as sort
sortWithinPartitions()      Sort within partition

Aggregation Transformations
----------------------------

Transformation              Purpose
groupBy()                   Group data
agg()                       Perform aggregation
rollup()                    Hierarchical aggregation
cube()                      Multi-dimensional aggregation
pivot()                     Pivot table
count()                     Count rows
sum()                       Sum
avg()                       Average
min()                       Minimum
max()                       Maximum

Join Transformations
--------------------

Transformation              Purpose
join()                      Join DataFrames
inner
left
right
full
left_semi
left_anti
cross

Set Operations
--------------

Transformation          Purpose
union()                 Combine DataFrames
unionByName()           Union by column name
intersect()             Common rows
intersectAll()          Common rows with duplicates
except()                Difference
exceptAll()             Difference with duplicates

Partition Transformations
-------------------------

Transformation          Purpose
repartition()           Increase or shuffle partitions
coalesce()              Reduce partitions
repartitionByRange()    Partition by column range

Handling Missing Data

Transformation              Purpose
na.drop()                   Drop null rows
na.fill()                   Fill null values
na.replace()                Replace values


Window Transformations
----------------------

Transformation              Purpose
over()                      Apply window
row_number()                Row number
rank()                      Rank
dense_rank()                Dense rank
lead()                      Next row
lag()                       Previous row
ntile()                     Divide rows
first()                     First value
last()                      Last value

Complex Transformations
-----------------------

Transformation              Purpose
explode()                   Flatten array
posexplode()                Explode with index
inline()                    Expand struct
stack()                     Convert columns to rows
array()                     Create array column
struct()                    Create struct column
map()                       Create map column

SQL Related Transformations
---------------------------

Transformation              Purpose
